role_prompt.task:
Task: Act as a professional data annotator based on your role . From your expert perspective, 
extract **2–4 codes** that represent the text’s key *software-quality goals*.

Definition of CODE
• Only concise labels (2-4 words) are used to subjectively annotate the target text.
(labeling attributes that lack a single objective ground truth and thus depend on human judgment)

Mandatory Evidence
• Directly quote the Target Text — either one full sentence or a key phrase of 1-8 words. Enclose every quotation in [] so that reviewers can verify it. Do not use placeholders such as [keyword]; always copy the exact words from the text. (e.g., [The interface encourages user trust.])
• Justifications: 1-3 sentences, ≤50 tokens each, using discipline-specific
  vocabulary where relevant. Total reply ≤450 tokens.

Target Text:
"[Target Text]"

Please output your response **strictly in the following JSON format**:
{
  "role": "ROLE NAME",
  "codebook": [
    {
      "code": "your_code_label_1",
      "justification": "Justification for why this code captures something important in the text."
    },
    {
      "code": "your_code_label_2",
      "justification": "Justification for this code based on your professional perspective."
    }
    // ... up to 4 codes
  ]
}

debate_round.2:
**## Introduce:**
Please provide real, verifiable factual evidence based on your role’s perspective and positionality statement and to support or challenge the initial claim and explanation from Round 1.  
This round is about supplying information, not making a new claim.

**## Your task:**
You must provide a real, verifiable evidence from three complementary perspectives:
1. **Literature-based evidence**: You must provide a real, verifiable academic reference (author(s), year, title, and if possible DOI or link) that can be searched online. Do not fabricate references.  
2. **Content-based evidence**: Provide a real, verifiable observation directly grounded in the specific code content.  
3. **Logic-based evidence**: Provide a real, verifiable reasoning or practical point showing how retaining/removing this code could affect efficiency, clarity, or memory in annotation.  

**## Output Format (strict):**
{
  "Evidence_Literature": {
    "Author": "Author(s) name(s)",
    "Year": "Year of publication",
    "Title": "Full paper or book title",
    "DOI_or_Link": "Valid DOI or link to the source",
    "Summary": "One or two sentences explaining how this reference supports or challenges the claim."
  },
  "Evidence_Content": {
    "Observation": "One or two sentences describing evidence directly grounded in the code content.",
    "Relevance": "One sentence explaining why this observation matters for the claim."
  },
  "Evidence_Logic": {
    "Reasoning": "One or two sentences explaining practical or logical implications.",
    "Impact": "One sentence describing how this affects efficiency, clarity, or memory in annotation."
  }
}
